metatags.apple-mobile-web-app-title: FactCheck.org - A Project of The Annenberg Public Policy Center
metatags.og:title: Social Media Posts Make Baseless Claim on COVID-19 Death Toll
metatags.og:description: Viral posts wrongly suggest that the COVID-19 death toll is exaggerated because "the state" has instructed that "anyone who didnt die by a gun shot wound or car accident" be listed as a coronavirus victim. Experts say there is no such default classification -- and that the U.S. death count is probably underestimated.

metatags.apple-mobile-web-app-title: FactCheck.org - A Project of The Annenberg Public Policy Center
metatags.og:title: Misinformation on COVID-19 Death Protocols in New York
metatags.og:description: A viral Facebook post about COVID-19 falsely claims that in New York "every contaminated corpse belongs to the state" and will be incinerated without any "wakes or memorial services to pay your last respects." The state is allowing funeral services with limited visitors; cremation is not mandated.
